		<label>greater bonewalker</label>
		<uiIconScale>1.35</uiIconScale>
		<description>A corpse reanimated through totally-not-necromancy, often found guarding Dunmer ancestral tombs. Significantly stronger than the lesser bonewalker, the curses inflicted by greater bonwalkers are far more dangerous, and require medical tending to cure.\n\nLike all undead creations, greater bonewalkers are completely immune to pain, a side effect of the reanimation process, which has also severly damaged their cognitive functions.\n\nBonewalkers often carry the brown rot disease, infecting any the creature attacks. Some specimens are instead capable of cursing their victims, greatly draining the victims strength or endurance.\n\nBonewalkers are willing to chase agressors until their legs fail them. Because of this, there are often special wards around the entrances of Dunmer tombs, preventing the bonewalkers from leaving. Similar results can be achieved using zones.</description>
